    • Method Detail

      • generateWeightedMidWalksForEntity

        List<String> generateWeightedMidWalksForEntity(String entity,
                                               int numberOfWalks,
                                               int depth)
        Weighted mid walk: If there are more options to go forward, it is more likely to go forward. The walks are duplicate free.
        Parameters:
        entity - The entity for which walks shall be generated.
        numberOfWalks - Number of walks to be performed per entity.
        depth - The depth of the walk. Depth is defined as hop to the next node. A walk of depth 1 will have three walk components.
        Returns:
        List of walks.
